# Tasks

All development workflows go through `uv run tasks <name>`. Run `uv run tasks help` for the full list.

## Core tasks

| Task | What it does |
|---|---|
| `lint` | Ruff lint (`src` + `tests` if present) |
| `lint:fix` | Ruff lint with auto-fix |
| `format` | Ruff format |
| `format:check` | Verify formatting without changes |
| `typecheck` | `ty` type check (`src`) |
| `test` | Run pytest (no-op when `tests/` is absent) |
| `test:cov` | pytest with coverage report |
| `watch` | pytest-watch for TDD |
| `security` | Bandit security scan |
| `radon:cc` | Cyclomatic complexity report |
| `radon:mi` | Maintainability-index report |
| `vulture` | Dead-code detection |

## Composites

| Task | Combines |
|---|---|
| `check` | `lint` + `typecheck` + `test` |
| `ci` | `format:check` + `lint` + `typecheck` + `test:cov` + `security` |
| `complexity` | `radon:cc` + `radon:mi` |

## Template maintenance

| Task | What it does |
|---|---|
| `update` | Pulls latest pyarnes template improvements (wraps `uvx copier update`) |

## Configuration

The `tasks` CLI reads `[tool.pyarnes-tasks]` from `pyproject.toml`:

```toml
[tool.pyarnes-tasks]
sources = ["src"]        # code roots — ruff / ty / bandit / radon / vulture targets
tests = ["tests"]         # pytest test roots (silently skipped if missing)
```

Missing paths are dropped from each command line, so `uv run tasks check` works on a freshly-scaffolded project that has no `tests/` yet.
